gomodel:SYNGO_1762  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: To examine the localization of the lamprey homologue of EHD1/3 they injected an Alexa 488-labeled lamprey-EHD antibody and an Alexa 546-labeled synaptotagmin antibody. The labeling of the two antibodies colocalized (Fig. 2H), thus showing that lamprey EHD is enriched at synaptic release sites.. Experimental description: From the abstract, \"We have investigated the role of an EHD1/3 ortholog (l-EHD) in the lamprey giant reticulospinal synapse\"" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
